Serializable
public class InvalidArgument
extends BELUncheckedException

BEL runtime exception indicating an invalid argument was provided.

This class should be used in favor of IllegalArgumentException as it forces a standard for runtime exception reporting.

Constructor Detail

InvalidArgument

@Deprecated
public InvalidArgument()
Deprecated. You should be explaining why the argument is invalid.

Creates an invalid argument exception with "Invalid argument" as its detail message. The cause is not initialized, and may subsequently be initialized by a call to Throwable.initCause(Throwable).

The constructors InvalidArgument(String) and InvalidArgument(String, Throwable) are favored in preference to using the default message.

InvalidArgument

Creates an invalid argument exception with the specified cause and "Invalid argument" as its detail message.
